eposteriorbelief\", \"from\": 3585, \"to\": 3603}, {\"ngram\": \"these probabilities\", \"from\": 3610, \"to\": 3629}, {\"ngram\": \"turn\", \"from\": 3641, \"to\": 3645}, {\"ngram\": \"the sporting development systems\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3698}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prior beliefs about this probability for a particular country can be deduced in many ways.\", \"from\": 3701, \"to\": 3791, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Prior beliefs\", \"from\": 3701, \"to\": 3714}, {\"ngram\": \"this probability\", \"from\": 3721, \"to\": 3737}, {\"ngram\": \"a particular country\", \"from\": 3742, \"to\": 3762}, {\"ngram\": \"many ways\", \"from\": 3781, \"to\": 3790}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In our case, we infer what might be expected in a particular country by examining the distribution of per-capita medal ratios across all other countries.\", \"from\": 3792, \"to\": 3945, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our case\", \"from\": 3795, \"to\": 3803}, {\"ngram\": \"a particular country\", \"from\": 3840, \"to\": 3860}, {\"ngram\": \"the distribution\", \"from\": 3874, \"to\": 3890}, {\"ngram\": \"capita\", \"from\": 3898, \"to\": 3904}, {\"ngram\": \"all other countries\", \"from\": 3925, \"to\": 3944}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In other words, if we had no specific knowledge pertaining to medal counts in a particular country of interest (for instance, in Ireland), the prior distribution describes the general distribution of medal winning probabilities around the world.\", \"from\": 3946, \"to\": 4191, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4075, \"end\": 4082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.999997749224608, \"rank\": 2.2507802664157694e-06, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other words\", \"from\": 3949, \"to\": 3960}, {\"ngram\": \"no specific knowledge\", \"from\": 3972, \"to\": 3993}, {\"ngram\": \"medal counts\", \"from\": 4008, \"to\": 4020}, {\"ngram\": \"a particular country\", \"from\": 4024, \"to\": 4044}, {\"ngram\": \"interest\", \"from\": 4048, \"to\": 4056}, {\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 4062, \"to\": 4070}, {\"ngram\": \"the prior distribution\", \"from\": 4085, \"to\": 4107}, {\"ngram\": \"the general distribution\", \"from\": 4118, \"to\": 4142}, {\"ngram\": \"medal winning probabilities\", \"from\": 4146, \"to\": 4173}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 4181, \"to\": 4190}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These vague prior beliefs are then combined with the country's medal count and population size to calculate the Bayes' (or posterior) estimate of the probability.\", \"from\": 4192, \"to\": 4354, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These vague prior beliefs\", \"from\": 4192, \"to\": 4217}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's medal count and population size\", \"from\": 4241, \"to\": 4286}, {\"ngram\": \"the Bayes' (or posterior) estimate\", \"from\": 4300, \"to\": 4334}, {\"ngram\": \"the probability\", \"from\": 4338, \"to\": 4353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When we run the model over the last five Olympic cycles, we see New Zealand outperforming almost all other nations In doing so, we assume that each citizen has a small independent chance of winning a medal according to this probability.\", \"from\": 4356, \"to\": 4593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4420, \"end\": 4431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5701178925562185, \"rank\": 0.7197271551322755, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the model\", \"from\": 4368, \"to\": 4377}, {\"ngram\": \"the last five Olympic cycles\", \"from\": 4383, \"to\": 4411}, {\"ngram\": \"almost all other nations\", \"from\": 4446, \"to\": 4470}, {\"ngram\": \"each citizen\", \"from\": 4499, \"to\": 4511}, {\"ngram\": \"a small independent chance\", \"from\": 4516, \"to\": 4542}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4561}, {\"ngram\": \"this probability\", \"from\": 4575, \"to\": 4591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the actual medal count is random, we would expect to observe a certain number of medals on average from a country if we were to repeat the Olympics many times.\", \"from\": 4594, \"to\": 4759, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the actual medal count\", \"from\": 4600, \"to\": 4622}, {\"ngram\": \"a certain number\", \"from\": 4661, \"to\": 4677}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 4681, \"to\": 4687}, {\"ngram\": \"a country\", \"from\": 4704, \"to\": 4713}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4735, \"to\": 4747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This process of combining prior beliefs with data will average out those once-off spikes and result in a downward adjustment to the per-capita medal ratios for smaller population countries at the top of the per-capita table, reflecting the fact that the exceptional performance in these countries in the 2024 Olympics is unlikely to be repeated in future Olympics.\", \"from\": 4760, \"to\": 5124, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This process\", \"from\": 4760, \"to\": 4772}, {\"ngram\": \"prior beliefs\", \"from\": 4786, \"to\": 4799}, {\"ngram\": \"data\", \"from\": 4805, \"to\": 4809}, {\"ngram\": \"those once-off spikes\", \"from\": 4827, \"to\": 4848}, {\"ngram\": \"a downward adjustment\", \"from\": 4863, \"to\": 4884}, {\"ngram\": \"capita\", \"from\": 4896, \"to\": 4902}, {\"ngram\": \"smaller population countries\", \"from\": 4920, \"to\": 4948}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 4952, \"to\": 4959}, {\"ngram\": \"capita\", \"from\": 4971, \"to\": 4977}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 4996, \"to\": 5004}, {\"ngram\": \"the exceptional performance\", \"from\": 5010, \"to\": 5037}, {\"ngram\": \"these countries\", \"from\": 5041, \"to\": 5056}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 5060, \"to\": 5077}, {\"ngram\": \"future Olympics\", \"from\": 5108, \"to\": 5123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The principle of a Bayesian ranking approach to Olympic medal tables is to order countries by the so-calledposteriorestimates of these probabilities.\", \"from\": 5126, \"to\": 5275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5145, \"end\": 5153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bayesian_probability\", \"score\": 0.9990164181759, \"rank\": 0.0009845482830270072, \"text\": \"Bayesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bayesian_probability\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bayesian_probability\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The principle\", \"from\": 5126, \"to\": 5139}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic medal tables\", \"from\": 5174, \"to\": 5194}, {\"ngram\": \"countries\", \"from\": 5207, \"to\": 5216}, {\"ngram\": \"the so-calledposteriorestimates\", \"from\": 5220, \"to\": 5251}, {\"ngram\": \"these probabilities\", \"from\": 5255, \"to\": 5274}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The results from our Bayesian ranking algorithm for the 2024 Olympic games puts New Zealand as top performer.\", \"from\": 5276, \"to\": 5385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5297, \"end\": 5305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bayesian_probability\", \"score\": 0.9990164181759, \"rank\": 0.0009845482830270072, \"text\": \"Bayesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bayesian_probability\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bayesian_probability\"}, {\"begin\": 5356, \"end\": 5367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5701178925562185, \"rank\": 0.7197271551322755, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The results\", \"from\": 5276, \"to\": 5287}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic games\", \"from\": 5328, \"to\": 5350}, {\"ngram\": \"top performer\", \"from\": 5371, \"to\": 5384}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, when we run the model over the last five Olympic cycles, we see New Zealand outperforming almost all other nations, providing evidence that this approach gives a sensible and stable measure of a countries' ability to develop Olympic medal winners.\", \"from\": 5386, \"to\": 5642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5459, \"end\": 5470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5701178925562185, \"rank\": 0.7197271551322755, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 5389, \"to\": 5393}, {\"ngram\": \"the model\", \"from\": 5407, \"to\": 5416}, {\"ngram\": \"the last five Olympic cycles\", \"from\": 5422, \"to\": 5450}, {\"ngram\": \"almost all other nations\", \"from\": 5485, \"to\": 5509}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 5521, \"to\": 5529}, {\"ngram\": \"this approach\", \"from\": 5535, \"to\": 5548}, {\"ngram\": \"a sensible and stable measure\", \"from\": 5555, \"to\": 5584}, {\"ngram\": \"a countries' ability\", \"from\": 5588, \"to\": 5608}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic medal winners\", \"from\": 5620, \"to\": 5641}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A lot of parallels can be drawn between New Zealand and Ireland: similar population sizes, average climate and stunning scenery.\", \"from\": 5648, \"to\": 5776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5688, \"end\": 5699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5701178925562185, \"rank\": 0.7197271551322755, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5704, \"end\": 5711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.999997749224608, \"rank\": 2.2507802664157694e-06, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A lot\", \"from\": 5648, \"to\": 5653}, {\"ngram\": \"parallels\", \"from\": 5657, \"to\": 5666}, {\"ngram\": \"similar population sizes\", \"from\": 5713, \"to\": 5737}, {\"ngram\": \"average climate\", \"from\": 5739, \"to\": 5754}, {\"ngram\": \"stunning scenery\", \"from\": 5759, \"to\": 5775}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However,Ireland has twice the GDP of New Zealandso we should have the advantage of more financial choice, but we consistently do worse.\", \"from\": 5777, \"to\": 5912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5785, \"end\": 5792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.999997749224608, \"rank\": 2.2507802664157694e-06, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"twice the GDP\", \"from\": 5797, \"to\": 5810}, {\"ngram\": \"New Zealandso\", \"from\": 5814, \"to\": 5827}, {\"ngram\": \"the advantage\", \"from\": 5843, \"to\": 5856}, {\"ngram\": \"more financial choice\", \"from\": 5860, \"to\": 5881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, what is New Zealand doing that we can learn from to develop our sporting talent?\", \"from\": 5913, \"to\": 5997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5925, \"end\": 5936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5701178925562185, \"rank\": 0.7197271551322755, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our sporting talent\", \"from\": 5977, \"to\": 5996}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New Zealand is known to have a strong sporting and outdoor culture, particularly from early childhood schooling, and excels internationally in sports like rugby, rowing and sailing.\", \"from\": 5999, \"to\": 6180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5999, \"end\": 6010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5701178925562185, \"rank\": 0.7197271551322755, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a strong sporting and outdoor culture\", \"from\": 6028, \"to\": 6065}, {\"ngram\": \"early childhood schooling\", \"from\": 6085, \"to\": 6110}, {\"ngram\": \"excels\", \"from\": 6116, \"to\": 6122}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 6142, \"to\": 6148}, {\"ngram\": \"rugby\", \"from\": 6154, \"to\": 6159}, {\"ngram\": \"rowing\", \"from\": 6161, \"to\": 6167}, {\"ngram\": \"sailing\", \"from\": 6172, \"to\": 6179}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not that Ireland does not have a strong sporting culture, but we focus much of our resources on Gaelic games which are not Olympic sports (not since 1904 at least).\", \"from\": 6181, \"to\": 6350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6195, \"end\": 6202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.999997749224608, \"rank\": 2.2507802664157694e-06, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a strong sporting culture\", \"from\": 6217, \"to\": 6242}, {\"ngram\": \"our resources\", \"from\": 6265, \"to\": 6278}, {\"ngram\": \"Gaelic games\", \"from\": 6282, \"to\": 6294}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic sports\", \"from\": 6309, \"to\": 6323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While this is extremely important to our cultural identity, it is unfortunate that we cannot showcase this sporting prowess on a global scale to the same extent as New Zealand do in the Olympic games.\", \"from\": 6351, \"to\": 6551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6515, \"end\": 6526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5701178925562185, \"rank\": 0.7197271551322755, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our cultural identity\", \"from\": 6388, \"to\": 6409}, {\"ngram\": \"this sporting prowess\", \"from\": 6453, \"to\": 6474}, {\"ngram\": \"a global scale\", \"from\": 6478, \"to\": 6492}, {\"ngram\": \"the same extent\", \"from\": 6496, \"to\": 6511}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic games\", \"from\": 6533, \"to\": 6550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity.\", \"from\": 6553, \"to\": 6720, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your consent\", \"from\": 6561, \"to\": 6573}, {\"ngram\": \"this rte-player contentWe\", \"from\": 6582, \"to\": 6607}, {\"ngram\": \"rte-player\", \"from\": 6612, \"to\": 6622}, {\"ngram\": \"extra content\", \"from\": 6633, \"to\": 6646}, {\"ngram\": \"cookies\", \"from\": 6660, \"to\": 6667}, {\"ngram\": \"your device\", \"from\": 6671, \"to\": 6682}, {\"ngram\": \"data\", \"from\": 6695, \"to\": 6699}, {\"ngram\": \"your activity\", \"from\": 6706, \"to\": 6719}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences From RT\\u00c9 Radio 1's Drivetime, Minister for Sport Thomas Byrne on the announcement of \\u20ac173m in funding for 35 sports projects At an even deeper level, New Zealand do not necessarily focus on high-profile events which are heavily invested in by richer countries such as the United States and Australia.\", \"from\": 6721, \"to\": 7106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6854, \"end\": 6866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Byrne_(Meath_politician)\", \"score\": 0.8878533441272815, \"rank\": 0.07453416149067153, \"text\": \"Thomas Byrne\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Byrne_(Meath_politician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Byrne_(Meath_politician)\"}, {\"begin\": 6956, \"end\": 6967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5701178925562185, \"rank\": 0.7197271551322755, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 7078, \"end\": 7091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9947014281184977, \"rank\": 0.005326634223779739, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 7096, \"end\": 7105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999970140528618, \"rank\": 1.7534651956249196e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their details\", \"from\": 6735, \"to\": 6748}, {\"ngram\": \"the content\", \"from\": 6773, \"to\": 6784}, {\"ngram\": \"Preferences\", \"from\": 6792, \"to\": 6803}, {\"ngram\": \"RT\\u00c9 Radio 1's Drivetime\", \"from\": 6809, \"to\": 6832}, {\"ngram\": \"Minister\", \"from\": 6834, \"to\": 6842}, {\"ngram\": \"the announcement\", \"from\": 6869, \"to\": 6885}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u20ac173m\", \"from\": 6889, \"to\": 6894}, {\"ngram\": \"funding\", \"from\": 6898, \"to\": 6905}, {\"ngram\": \"35 sports projects\", \"from\": 6910, \"to\": 6928}, {\"ngram\": \"an even deeper level\", \"from\": 6932, \"to\": 6952}, {\"ngram\": \"high-profile events\", \"from\": 6994, \"to\": 7013}, {\"ngram\": \"richer countries\", \"from\": 7047, \"to\": 7063}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, they make focused decisions for their limited total funding towards the events and athletes where they have the greatest probability of success.\", \"from\": 7107, \"to\": 7260, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"focused decisions\", \"from\": 7126, \"to\": 7143}, {\"ngram\": \"their limited total funding\", \"from\": 7148, \"to\": 7175}, {\"ngram\": \"the events\", \"from\": 7184, \"to\": 7194}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 7199, \"to\": 7207}, {\"ngram\": \"the greatest probability\", \"from\": 7224, \"to\": 7248}, {\"ngram\": \"success\", \"from\": 7252, \"to\": 7259}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, they have a very tough qualifying standard for the games: only sending athletes that they believe can achieve a top 16 placing.\", \"from\": 7261, \"to\": 7401, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 7265, \"to\": 7272}, {\"ngram\": \"a very tough qualifying standard\", \"from\": 7284, \"to\": 7316}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 7321, \"to\": 7330}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 7345, \"to\": 7353}, {\"ngram\": \"a top 16 placing\", \"from\": 7384, \"to\": 7400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In their words, they aim for the best bang for their buck.\", \"from\": 7402, \"to\": 7460, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their words\", \"from\": 7405, \"to\": 7416}, {\"ngram\": \"the best bang\", \"from\": 7431, \"to\": 7444}, {\"ngram\": \"their buck\", \"from\": 7449, \"to\": 7459}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, there are issues with such targeted funding decisions as they may not deliver as many benefits to wider society as investing in sports where medals are harder to get.\", \"from\": 7461, \"to\": 7636, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"issues\", \"from\": 7480, \"to\": 7486}, {\"ngram\": \"such targeted funding decisions\", \"from\": 7492, \"to\": 7523}, {\"ngram\": \"as many benefits\", \"from\": 7548, \"to\": 7564}, {\"ngram\": \"wider society\", \"from\": 7568, \"to\": 7581}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 7598, \"to\": 7604}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 7611, \"to\": 7617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland is a wealthier country and we should, in theory, be able to match New Zealand's resources for Olympic talent development, while also supporting Gaelic games.\", \"from\": 7638, \"to\": 7803, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7638, \"end\": 7645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.999997749224608, \"rank\": 2.2507802664157694e-06, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 7712, \"end\": 7723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5701178925562185, \"rank\": 0.7197271551322755, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 7790, \"end\": 7802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaelic_games\", \"score\": 0.9531786374504524, \"rank\": 0.04912128819313901, \"text\": \"Gaelic games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaelic_games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaelic_games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a wealthier country\", \"from\": 7649, \"to\": 7668}, {\"ngram\": \"theory\", \"from\": 7687, \"to\": 7693}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic talent development\", \"from\": 7740, \"to\": 7766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With Budget 2025allocatinga sports fund of \\u20ac230 million euro to develop our sports infrastructure (up 50% on two years ago) we may start to see improvements in our Olympic performance, reflecting the potential of our country.\", \"from\": 7804, \"to\": 8029, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Budget 2025allocatinga sports fund\", \"from\": 7809, \"to\": 7843}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u20ac230 million euro\", \"from\": 7847, \"to\": 7864}, {\"ngram\": \"our sports infrastructure\", \"from\": 7876, \"to\": 7901}, {\"ngram\": \"improvements\", \"from\": 7948, \"to\": 7960}, {\"ngram\": \"our Olympic performance\", \"from\": 7964, \"to\": 7987}, {\"ngram\": \"the potential\", \"from\": 8000, \"to\": 8013}, {\"ngram\": \"our country\", \"from\": 8017, \"to\": 8028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But to make the most of this investment, we need to base our decisions on sound statistical evidence and answer such questions as 'who's doing well at developing their sporting talent that we can learn from?\", \"from\": 8031, \"to\": 8238, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this investment\", \"from\": 8055, \"to\": 8070}, {\"ngram\": \"our decisions\", \"from\": 8088, \"to\": 8101}, {\"ngram\": \"sound statistical evidence\", \"from\": 8105, \"to\": 8131}, {\"ngram\": \"such questions\", \"from\": 8143, \"to\": 8157}, {\"ngram\": \"their sporting talent\", \"from\": 8193, \"to\": 8214}]}, {\"sentence\": \";, 'what sports and disciplines should we best invest in, to better our society or improve Olympic medal performance?'\", \"from\": 8238, \"to\": 8356, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"what sports\", \"from\": 8242, \"to\": 8253}, {\"ngram\": \"disciplines\",